The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning method for multiobjective optimization, which involves modeling each subproblem with an attention model that can exploit both node features and structure features of input nodes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and systems and control (cs.SY).
